        "text": "Listen to This Episode!\n\nListen as we visit James Madison’s birth and site at Belle Grove Plantation in Port Conway, along the Rappahannock. While the original home fell into the river (!), you can visit the current Belle Grove Plantation. Learn about Madison’s childhood and education, his family, and what else happened near his birth site!\n\nHistory of Belle Grove Plantation, on the site of the President’s birthplace.\n\nJames Madison at Mount Pleasant from Encyclopedia Virginia.\n\nBe sure to check out James Madison’s “Visiting the Presidents” Episode from Season 2, “James Madison and Montpelier” for his homes!\n\nAlso, check out James Madison’s “Visiting the Presidents” Episode from Season 3, “James Madison’s Tomb” for his gravesite!\n\nFrom My May 2017 Visit!\n\n***BONUS: the Booth markers I spotted en route to the Madison birthplace!\n\nFrom My July 2021 Visit!\n\nFrom My June 2022 Visit!\n\nJames Madison Birthplace: 17200 James Madison Parkway, Port Conway, Virginia.\n\nCheck out the Most Recent Episodes!\n\nRecommended Reading for James Madison\n\nFeldman, Noah. The Three Lives of James Madison: Genius, Partisan, President\n\nKetcham, Ralph. James Madison: A Biography"
